2. International Rescue Committee (IRC) - provides emergency relief, rehabilitation, and long-term development programs in response to complex crises and disasters, including refugees and internally displaced people.
3. Oxfam International - works to right the wrongs of poverty, inequality, and injustice, focusing on emergency response, food security, and climate resilience, as well as advocating for policy changes that benefit the poor and marginalized
